WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.640
What you're watching right now is not a video file.

00:00:03.220 --> 00:00:05.520
No pixels are streaming, there's no codec.

00:00:06.040 --> 00:00:09.440
This is a React component, mounted inside a video player,

00:00:09.720 --> 00:00:11.360
synced to the sound of my voice.

00:00:12.600 --> 00:00:14.680
The audio is the only real file here.

00:00:15.240 --> 00:00:18.220
As I speak, named cues fire on word boundaries

00:00:18.220 --> 00:00:19.760
and the visuals react to them.

00:00:20.420 --> 00:00:21.500
Go ahead, pause me.

00:00:22.020 --> 00:00:22.740
Scrub the timeline.

00:00:23.380 --> 00:00:25.840
Every frame you see is live DOM.

00:00:27.040 --> 00:00:29.540
Because it's just markup, it is resolution independent.

00:00:30.200 --> 00:00:34.140
4K, a retina laptop, a phone, all pixel perfect.

00:00:34.640 --> 00:00:37.260
These subtitles come from the same word timings.

00:00:37.500 --> 00:00:39.020
And when the author edits a scene,

00:00:39.260 --> 00:00:40.580
there is nothing to re-render.
